  25. external id : < .. > -> int = "%field1"
  26. (** Return an integer identifying this object, unique for
  27.     the current execution of the program. The generic comparison
  28.     and hashing functions are based on this integer. When an object
  29.     is obtained by unmarshaling, the id is refreshed, and thus
  30.     different from the original object. As a consequence, the internal
  31.     invariants of data structures such as hash table or sets containing
  32.     objects are broken after unmarshaling the data structures.
  33.   *)
